The paper deals with the problem of estimating the maximum matching size in graph streams, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithm design. The paper presents new upper and lower bound results for both insertion-only streams and dynamic streams. The problem is related to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
